# GameHub Java


### Folder Structure

```
GameHub/                              ← Git repo root
│
├── .gitignore                        ← Provided at end of this guide
├── README.md                         ← Optional description
│
├── src/
│   └── Jason/                        ← Java package (must match "package Jason;")
│       │
│       ├── MainLauncher.java         ← MAIN FILE — runs the whole app (sidebar UI)
│       ├── GameHub.java              ← Alternative tabbed launcher (keep both)
│       │
│       ├── MathsQuiz.java            ← Standalone (testing only)
│       ├── MathsQuizPanel.java       ← ✅ Used in launcher (BUG FIXED)
│       │
│       ├── SeaBattle.java            ← Standalone (testing only)
│       ├── SeaBattlePanel.java       ← ✅ Used in launcher
│       │
│       ├── TicTacToe.java            ← Standalone (testing only)
│       ├── TicTacToePanel.java       ← ✅ Used in launcher
│       │
│       ├── FlappyBird.java           ← ✅ Used in launcher (ADD package Jason;)
│       │                                 (ADD Flappy.jpeg as bird face)
│       │
│       ├── TwoPlayerShooter.java     ← Standalone (testing only, ADD package Jason;)
│       ├── TwoPlayerShooterPanel.java ← ✅ NEW FILE — used in launcher
│       │                                  (uses Gun1.jpeg, Gun2.jpeg)
│       │
│       └── images/                   ← ALL image + audio assets go HERE
│           ├── Flappy.jpeg           ← Bird sprite (friend's face photo)
│           ├── Gun1.jpeg             ← Player 1 shooter sprite
│           ├── Gun2.jpeg             ← Player 2 shooter sprite
│           ├── ship.png              ← Any small PNG for sea battle hits
│           ├── hit.wav               ← Sound for sea battle hit
│           └── miss.wav              ← Sound for sea battle miss
│
└── bin/                              ← Auto-created when compiling (DO NOT edit)
    └── Jason/
        └── *.class files go here
```

### Step 1 — Install Java Extension Pack in VS Code
1. Open VS Code
2. Press `Ctrl+Shift+X` to open Extensions
3. Search: **Extension Pack for Java** (by Microsoft)
4. Click Install — this installs 6 extensions at once:
   - Language Support for Java
   - Debugger for Java
   - Maven for Java
   - Project Manager for Java
   - Test Runner
   - IntelliCode

### Step 2 — Install JDK if not already done
**Windows:**
- Download JDK 17 from: https://adoptium.net
- Install with default settings
- VS Code will auto-detect it

**Verify in terminal:**
```bash
java -version
javac -version
```
Both should show version 17 or higher.

### Step 3 — Open the Project
1. `File → Open Folder` → select your `GameHub/` folder
2. VS Code will detect Java files and show "Java Projects" in the Explorer sidebar
3. It may ask to set up — click "Yes"

### Step 4 — VS Code `settings.json` for Java source path
Press `Ctrl+Shift+P` → type "Open Workspace Settings JSON" → add:

```json
{
    "java.project.sourcePaths": ["src"],
    "java.project.outputPath": "bin",
    "java.project.referencedLibraries": []
}
```

This tells VS Code: source code is in `src/`, compile output goes to `bin/`.
